args: Well, that was quite the lively dinner.
I'm pleased my last attempt was such a\nglowing success. The villagers all seemed\nto enjoy my cooking a great deal.
This is the first time anyone has ever\npraised me for something besides\ndelivering Lady Amaterasu's word.
Lady Yukimura was right: I just had to\nkeep trying in order to find success.\nAnd now I want to try even more!

*yaaaawn* But first, it's time for sleep.
Since I no longer give nightly reports,
there's no need to make myself stay
awake until the wee hours.
Is this...Takamagahara? But how did I get\nhere? Also, Takamagahara is gone now!
Oh, right. I fell asleep in the village,\nwhich means this is but a dream.\nAnd if it IS a dream...
Why, if it isn't Izumo. What has you so\nelated? Did something wonderful happen?
Yes, it did! Though small, I took part in an\nimportant experience that helped me move\nforward all on my own.
I have been trying and trying to change the\nfact I was useless, and I finally succeeded.
I never knew how wonderful success could\nfeel after struggling for so long.
I am so glad to hear it.
I must have really wanted to tell you this\nif I came all the way here in a dream.
Especially since you're no longer here...
So no matter how much I talk to you in my\ndreams, it doesn't really matter.
You are correct that I am but a shadow\nof myself reflected in your dream.
However, it still gladdens me to know\nhow much you've grown.
Such joy makes me want to take you\nout of this dream world all the more,\nwhich is why I have come.
Now return to the real world, my emissary.\nThe time for your awakening has come.
*gasp* J-just a dream, I guess.\nStill, what she said...
Huh? That sound came from outside!
Aaaah! Please stop, whoever you are!\nStay back from our village!
Go, my Mukuroshu brethren! Ransack this\nvillage until you find what we came for!
NICE TRY, CHUMPSTAIN! But you ain't\nlaying a finger on anyone here so long\nas I'm around! HYAAAAAAAH!
Hah! Even a Wyrmclan leader can't hope\nto stand against out superior numbers!
Why are the Mukuroshu here?! ...No,\nthat doesn't matter now. I must aid\nLady Yukimura in her fight, or else—
Well, well! Here I'd thought reinforcements\nhad arrived, but it appears it's just the\nmain course. Stay your hands, boys!
You put your weapons away? If this is\nsome kinda trick, I won't fall for it!
Our goal was simply to negotiate with the\nemissary of Amaterasu.
Yes. We seek your power—the one you\nused to resurrect our Lady Tsukuyomi.
We do not wish you harm. I swear it.
If you are willing to come quietly with us,\nwe will leave this village in peace.

Seems like a fair deal to me. You get safe
passage, and all your friends get to live—
including that fighter lady there who's
clearly down to her last leg.
Don't listen to him! I'm totally fine!\nI just need to go full hardcore and—GAH!
Rude! I'm trying to have a conversation!\n...Now then, emissary. What say you?
This is all my fault, and I will do what\nI must to keep everyone from harm.
Glad to see you have a good head on your\nshoulders. Right this way then, if you will?\nStep lively, now!
No, emissary! You mustn't go with them!
D-don't yield to that terrible person!\nFight back!
How can you say that when you're so\nclearly afraid of these people?
Oh, these brutes are terrifying, and no\nmistake—but I'm even more scared at\nthe thought of losing you.
You are our hope, emissary, and no matter\nhow afraid I may be, I will stand tall if it\nmeans keeping you safe!
How can you say such a thing about a\npathetic person like myself?!
I've done NOTHING for you save the kinds\nof tasks you'd pat a small child on the\nhead for!
I am a blight upon this village who brought\nnaught but disaster upon you all, so why\nwould you risk your lives for me?!
Because we Hinomotoans have always\nbeen lifted up by you.

Whenever disaster struck, you always
appeared with messages from Lady
Amaterasu, and your words brought us
great comfort in those dark times.
And now you have come to us and offered\nyour assistance. You sought to understand\nour feelings and walk in our shoes.
Even if Lady Amaterasu is no longer with\nus, you still remain—and we want you to\nremain with us forever!
You are the hope of all Hinomoto, and with\nyou, we can stand against any threat!
Izumo, there is a task that only you—\nan emissary of Amaterasu—can do.

So if you still wish to face some form of
judgment, then live. Live and carry out
your duty as her emissary. That is the best
way for you to atone to the people.
(The villagers' words were the answer\nI've been looking for this entire time!)
(THIS is the duty only I can perform!)
Thank you, everyone. I understand now.
Yes. If I am to stand alongside you all,\nI cannot sacrifice myself now.
I refuse your offer, Mukuroshu.\nI will not take one step with you.

Furthermore, I swear on my name as the
emissary of Amaterasu to join forces with
my people, drive your vile kind from our
midst, and save this village!
You're a damn fool, boy! However\ndetermined you may be, a puppet\nof a dead Amaterasu is useless!
But fine. If that's how you want it,\nwe'll just kill everyone else here and\nTAKE what we want! Get 'em, boys!
Uh, boss? Is it just me, or is the sky\nstarting to...glow?
And are those storm clouds moving in...?\nN-no! That's impossible! The sky was\nclear just a second ago!
